page.title: 10Macclesfield Forest - Flora
page.content:
{Flora}- The following varieties of wild flowers may be found in the Churchyard:-
Daisy, Field Buttercup, Sweet Cicely, Rhododendron, Red Hawkweed (Fox and Cubs), Ox-eye Daisy, Heath Bedstraw, Red Clover, White Clover, Zig-zag Clover, Hogweed, Common Cat's Ear, Lady's Mantle, Bird's Eye Speedwell, Bilberry, Butter Dock, Yarrow, London Pride, Common Sorrel, Ribwort Plantain, Mouse-ear Hawkweed, Meadow Pea, Sheep's Fescue, Woodrush, Cock's-foot, Brown Bent, Tufted Vetch, Meadow Vetchling, Japanese Knotweed, Wavy Hairgrass, Creeping Soft Grass, Yorkshire Fog, Sweet Verral Grass, Sycamore, Elder, Nettle, Timothy Grass.
